heaviest_rainfall.status: Today ranked 7th for the heaviest total rainfall during a storm, dropping a total of 23.86mm of rain over the storm duration of 31.0 hours with a maximum rate of 8.3mm per hour.  The largest amount of rain ever recorded is on 09 November 2025 when 47.89mm fell at a maximum rate of 24.6mm per hour over the 144.8 hour event.

heaviest_rainrate.status: The 2nd ranked rain rate was recorded today with a peak rate of 27.6mm per hour, highlighting an extreme precipitation event.  6.1mm of rain fell during the storm's 2.6 hours length.  A torrential downpour occurred on 02 September 2025 when the rain reached a maximum intensity of 34.3mm per hour.  This happened during a 15.0 hour storm when 21.19mm of rain fell.

longest_rain.status: Today's rainstorm ranked 7th on our record table for the length of the storm as it lasted 31.0 hours; it delivered 23.86mm of rain at a maximum rate of 8.3mm per hour.  Rain fell for 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025 creating a new record that still lasts.  The storm produced a total of 47.89mm with a maximum intensity of 24.6mm per hour.
